text: Port Angeles is a town in the state of Washington. It is the county seat of Clallam County, Washington, and is its largest settlement. ==Media== The local newspaper is the Peninsula Daily News, at first the Port Angeles Evening News (founded 1916). The Peninsula Daily News publishes 6 days a week and hosts a website for the North Olympic Peninsula. Newsradio 1450 KONP has news, sports, information and talk programming. The Strait 102 KSTI is an FM radio station playing country music in the area. ==Gallery== ==References== Category:Cities in Washington (state) Category:County seats in Washington (state)
